roadav
@Assa There is 3 different stances, Stance #1, Stance #2, Stance #3.
They are all very verry rare and doesen't help you with anything, They're just cool

While they look good while in their idle animation, the game is designed to work with the default stances. So, transitions between those stances and walking/attacking are jarring. Also, if a Brute with a rare stance does a counter attack, it gets stuck in the default stance (since counter attacks don't activate the idle stance afterwards)

To conclude, the rare stances are neat, but you don't get to really enjoy them. Too many things look weird, and Brutes don't stay in their idle animation for that long
